tique contemporary practices in sport history, the contributors raise the level of critical analysis of the production of historical knowledge, provide examples of approaches by those who have struggled with or adapted to the postmodern challenge, and open up new avenues for future sport historians to follow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aSportsxHistory. 0aSportsxSociological aspects. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / History.2bisacsh1 aBale, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBooth, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, CL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHutchins, Brett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMessner, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMunslow, Alun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOriard, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParratt, Catriona M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Murray G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillips, Murray G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPope, S. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRinehart, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSydnor, Synthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVertinsky, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z9783